         <p>The materials are open for research.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_0c4ce14980d793ebbac4c19b4d95040d">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Mussolini Collection of V. Lada-Mocarski. Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_08bac8a6989e22e0c1d18b0700be065f">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This is a collection of research notes, manuscript drafts, correspondence, photographs and printed material about the days just prior to and after the execution of Mussolini in April of 1945, assembled by V. Lada-Mocarski for a magazine article, "The Last Three Days of Mussolini," <title render="italic">
               <part>Atlantic Monthly</part>
            </title>, December 1945. In 1945 Mr. Lada-Mocarski was in the O.S.S. in Switzerland and was granted permission to enter Italy right after the execution. He was able to obtain many eyewitness accounts.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
